Legislative_Speeches_Amazon

Cristiana Maglia & Lucas de Oliveira Paes

2023-07-19

Discursive coalitions on the Amazon in Brazil’s Parliamentary Debates

The Amazon houses unparalleled biodiversity and plays a crucial role in regulating climate. The region has already faced innumerous environmental threats, such as deforestation, illegal logging and land encroachment. These issues are being discussed in various fora in the political sphere, especially in the countries that are adjacent to the rainforest.

One of these fora is the Brazilian Congress. Amazonian issues have sparked debates within the lower chamber, where policymakers from multiple political parties, regions and interest groups engage in discussions. One way to analyze the disputes around Amazon is focusing on the speeches of representatives. In this project, I analyze their discursive engagement on the floor of the House of Representatives, from 2002 to 2020, in order to comprehend the dynamics of environmental policy decision and policy making regarding the governance of the Amazon, considering how ideologies and interests help to shape them in Brazil.

This project also aims to explore the discursive coalitions that have emerged within Brazilian HP, focusing on the debates concerning the Amazon, shedding light on the key actors and their arguments on the governance of the region.

First, we scrappe the website to collected the speeches given on the floor of the Brazilian House of Representatives/Câmara dos Deputados.
